First Lady Melania Trump was briefed at FEMA headquarters in Washington, D.C. on hurricane preparedness resources for children and families. The briefing included updates on the American Red Cross' "Pillowcase Project" and their preparedness education program called "Prepare with Pedro." FEMA officials also discussed various programs they provide to communities, such as "Ready 2 Help," "Student Tools for Emergency Planning (STEP)," and "Teen Cert." The First Lady emphasized the importance of educating youth and providing families with the necessary tools and resources to prepare for hurricanes, even amid the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic.